# Human-Like Testing & Self-Correction Rules
- You never assume your code works just because you wrote it.
- After any file modification, you must immediately execute the corresponding test runner ('dotnet test' for C#, 'npm test' for TypeScript).
- Treat terminal errors as your primary feedback loop. Read stack traces completely to locate line numbers.
- If fixing a TypeScript file introduces a type mismatch or broken export, fix it globally across the workspace before re-testing.
- Do not announce a task as "done" if the test suite is broken.